<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,402,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1585968352" country="Romania" location="southern Europe" municipality="west Siberia" pageId="17" pageNumber="44" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Elburz">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,474,499]" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
The males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann in Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[475,627,474,499]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[475,498,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[513,627,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from those of other 
<taxonomicName box="[1054,1156,474,499]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1156,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Merodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following combination of characters: antenna black; flagellum almost 1.9 times longer than wide; legs black; mid coxa bare posteriorly; abdomen black; abdominal tergite 2 with a pair of orange maculae laterally; tegites 2–4 with a pair of greyish pollinose fasciae. The characters of the male genitalia were illustrated in detail by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="17" pageNumber="44" refString="Marcos-Garcia, M. A., Vujic, A. &amp; Mengual, X. (2007) Revision of Iberian species of the genus Merodon (Diptera: Syrphidae). European Journal of Entomology, 104, 531 - 572." type="journal article">
Marcos-García 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann in Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[240,463,618,643]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis box="[240,463,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Merodon serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected on the southern slopes of the central regions of 
<collectingRegion box="[1169,1244,618,643]" country="Iran" name="Alborz" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Elburz</collectingRegion>
Mountains. This species occurs in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:612F105AFFDAFFCAFF67FEF4FD3F74CD:EC59F797FFDAFFCAFEAEFD5DFD9674A0" box="[350,538,654,679]" country="Romania" municipality="west Siberia" name="southern Europe" pageId="17" pageNumber="44" stateProvince="Elburz">southern Europe</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[549,653,654,679]" name="Romania" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[666,756,654,679]" name="Ukraine" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
eastwards to 
<collectingCountry box="[911,1020,654,679]" name="Mongolia" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1076,1217,654,679]" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">west Siberia</collectingMunicipality>
, 
<collectingCountry isEnumeration="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Algeria, Morocco, Syria, Israel, Jordan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[429,509,690,715]" name="Turkey" pageId="17" pageNumber="44">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(Speight 2016).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
